1.vi : older one - for everything we need to use commad, now-a-days it is anot recommended
2.vim : newer
  click "i" for insert
  for saving ":wq!"
3.nano: newer
  for saving crl+o then enter then control+x
  for copying "alt+a then right arrows then alt+^ for copying"
  for pasting "ctrl+u"
  for page down - alt+\
  for page up - alt+/
  
